messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full HTTP request path:
- /profiles/{id}

All HTTP methods acceptable:
- false

HTTP methods accepted for this endpoint (based on the code):
- HEAD: false
- POST: false
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: true
- PUT: false
- DELETE: true
- PATCH: true

Explanation:
- The main app mounts the profiles router with app.use('/profiles', profile) in index.js, so all routes declared in routes/profile.js are prefixed with /profiles.
- In routes/profile.js the route that maps to the controller getProfile is router.get('/:id', getProfile). Combined with the prefix that yields /profiles/:id; path parameters are shown as {id} so the full path is /profiles/{id}.
- The routes file registers handlers for the path segment ':id' for GET, PATCH and DELETE:
  - router.get('/:id', getProfile) → GET allowed.
  - router.patch('/:id', updateProfile) → PATCH allowed.
  - router.delete('/:id', deleteProfile) → DELETE allowed.
- There are no explicit handlers in the code for HEAD, POST, OPTIONS, TRACE, PUT at the /profiles/:id path, nor is there any router.all or middleware that would make "all methods" true. Per the instruction to base determination on the code (not on runtime framework behavior), those methods are marked false.
- Therefore only GET, PATCH and DELETE are explicitly accepted for /profiles/{id}.
